26:
Wh-what happened to Ayumu and
Nao?!
31:
Worry not, they are among friends.
They safely made it to our base of
operation.
33:
We would like to send you there as
well. I understand you just woke up,
but could you follow us?
42:
...That's enough. It's clear you won't
be able to take another step. I
apologize for pushing you too far.
51:
We will find another way to get you
to safety. If we can just secure the
lance, the gaps in this world should—
57:
What's the point of continuing... We
all saw what's beyond those gaps...
61:
The world has ended! Nothing you
or I do will fix—
66: And yet you still tried to help Nao.
73:
You're wrong. I'm not that good of a
person...
75: All I wanted to do was run away.
84:
...If it is permission you are looking
for, then I shall grant it.
85:
Once you are safe, be sure to
protect what is important to you.
89:
You know, you're a little too good at
lying.
92:
What was it you said about Alk back
when he was Ayumu? That it looked
like he wanted to be alone?
94: Is that REALLY how you saw him?
103: I know, I know. I'm just as bad.
106:
But Teach... Just how far are you
willing to go to believe your own lies?
110:
...It's too late. What could I possibly
do now...
114:
Mr. Takamori, you should hide
somewhere safe for now. I promise
we'll come find you once we figure
out how to save everyone.
118:
That... I can do. You take care,
Ayumu.
130:
Not everyone is fine with standing
on the sidelines and saving their
own behind, Mr. Takamori. But you
wouldn't know that, would you?
134:
Only seeing what you want to see...
Pretending like you don't know the
truth because it's more convenient
that way!
138:
Somehow I'm not surprised to hear
you say that...
153:
I-I don't have powers like the others.
There's nothing I can—
156: No! No, stop! Get away from meee!
172:
Kenny-poo, get me outta here! You
saw it too, right?! That rat was HUGE!
174:
You don't think it's that talking,
floating rat everyone's talking about,
right?! Right?! Ohhh, I hate rodents!
176:
Can it, Mika. All your screaming is
attracting attention.
186:
My sincerest apologies... I
completely misunderstood the
situation...
189:
You said you're a teacher, right? The
hell were you thinking? You don't
look like you've got powers. How
exactly were you gonna help
anybody?
190:
Still... Gotta say, it was pretty cool
seeing you rush in like that.
192:
Yeah, and with those glasses, you're
like a superhero in disguise.
194:
Well, we better get going. See ya
'round!
199: Wh-why are you being so nice?
206:
I always pretended I didn't see or
hear anything wrong. I wanted to
think that I was a good person!
210:
But I... I was just looking for an
excuse to do nothing!
213:
Well, you came to my rescue, didn't
you?
215:
Not sure what you're going through,
but don't let 'em see you sweat,
Teach.
217:
Still, I guess some teachers do cry in
front of their students... Just don't do
it all the time, okay?
220:
*sigh* A cool teacher would never
do something so embarrassing...
226: I suppose I have to start somewhere!
